The paper proposes a method for detecting curvilinear structures in images, which is a common problem in computer vision. The method uses brain-inspired trainable B-COSFIRE filters, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE). The paper also mentions the application of the method to medical image analysis, remote sensing, biometrics, and robotics, which suggests a broad range of potential sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
